Simple Text Editor = Data Structure Project1

Student: Anxhela Likcani
Project1 

1.Read and organize the dictionary 

For this project, I used a plain text file that contains 10000 words taken from the book "Alice in Wonderland". The file is stored inside the data folder. 
The program reads the file using the TextFileReader class. Each word is converted to lowercase and punctuation is removed. After reading the words, the list is sorted alphabetically. 

2. Upload words into the SinglyLinkedList 
After reading and sorting the words, all 10000 words are uploaded into a SinglyLinkedList.
This is done using addLast method.

The output confirms:
Words uploaded into SinglyLinkedList: 10000

3. Upload words into the Double Linked List

The same 10000 words are also uploaded into Double Linked List.

This is also done using the addLast method and the output confirms it:
Words uploaded into Double Linked List: 10000

4. Singly Linked List operations

The SinglyLinkedList class includes two required methods:
makeUnion
This method returns the union of two sorted singly linked lists.

intersect
This method returns the intersection of two sorted singly linked lists.

5.Double Linked List implementations

For the DoubleLinkedList part, I implemented two versions:

DoubleLinkedListHeaderNoTail
This version has a header node but no tail node.

DoubleLinkedListTailNoHeader
This version has a tail node but no header node.

6.Divide and load the data

The 10000 words are divided into two halves. 
First half: 5000 wrods
Second half: 5000 words

Each half is uploaded into a different SinglyLinkedList.
These two lists are then used to test makeUnion and interesect.


7. Test Class
The project is tested using:

weiss.nonstandart.TestProgam

This class tests:

-Reading the text file
-Uploading words into the singly linked list
-Uploading words into the double linked list
-Splitting the data into two halves
-Testing makeUnion
-Testing intersect
-Testing  the header/no-tail double linked list
-Testing the tail/no-header double linked list 

8.Expected output

The program should now:

Words read and sorted: 10000
Words uploaded into SinglyLinkedList: 10000
Words uploaded into the DoubleLinkedList: 10000
First half size: 5000
Second half size: 5000
Union size: 10000
Intersection size: 0
Header but no tail size: 10000
Tail but no header size: 10000


9. Conclusion

This project successfully reads a plain text file, process the words, stores them in linked list data structures, and test the required list operations. 
